<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-2978] Upgrade benchmark from commons-compress-1.0 to commons-compress-1.1 for 15 times faster gzip decompression</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-2978</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;In &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1540&quot; title=&quot;Improvements to contrib.benchmark for TREC collections&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-1540&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; TrecContentSource moved from Java&apos;s GZipInputStream to common-compress 1.0. &lt;br/&gt;
This slowed down gzip decompression by a factor of 15. &lt;br/&gt;
Upgrading to 1.1 solves this problem.&lt;br/&gt;
I verified that the problem is only in GZIP, not in BZIP.&lt;br/&gt;
On the way, as 1.1 introduced constants for the compression methods, the code can be made a bit nicer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
